<span id="page_145">p. 145</span>

#### <span class="smallcaps">The Seventh Tablet of the Story of the Creation</span>

<span class="smallcaps">Obverse</span>

1\. At that time the gods in their assembly created (the beasts).  
2. They made perfect the mighty (monsters).  
3. They caused the living creatures (of the field) to come forth,  
4 the cattle of the field, (the wild beasts) of the field and the
creeping things (of the field).  
5. (They fixed their habitations) for the living creatures (of the
field).  
6. They distributed <span id="fr_291"></span>[1](#fn_289.md) (in their
dwelling-places) the cattle and the creeping things of the city.  
7, (They made strong) the multitude of creeping things, all the
offspring (of the earth).  
8. …… in the assembly of my family.  
9. …… <span class="smallcaps">Ea</span> the god of the illustrious
face.  
10. … the multitude of creeping things did I make strong.  
11. … the seed of <span class="smallcaps">Lakhama</span> did I destroy.

*The rest is lost*.

